  "dateModified": "2026-03-06",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Restorative justice is an approach to harm that centers repair over punishment. Instead of asking \u0026ldquo;what law was broken, who broke it, and what punishment do they deserve?\u0026rdquo; restorative justice asks \u0026ldquo;who was harmed, what are their needs, and whose obligation is it to meet those needs?\u0026rdquo; The shift reframes the legal response to harm from a procedure directed at the offender to a process directed at the relationship between offender, victim, and community.\n",
